{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"22f0ed55-37f9-4d46-b5e4-1120c9cdfc22","content":"`.testsettings` files are **not supported** in MSTest v3. You need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file. Here's what your `local.testsettings` configures and how each part migrates:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `TestTimeout` (30s) | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>` or `[Timeout]` attribute |\n| Code Coverage DataCollector | `<DataCollectionRunSettings><DataCollectors>` |\n| `AssemblyResolution / useLoadContext` | No longer needed — MSTest v3 runs from the output directory by default |\n\nLet me create the replacement `.runsettings` file and update the project:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_017BvFFxPmFHVUVrhqZ2vyKg","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Creating runsettings replacement"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01D1sTMAiSGDWjuQW7jEH3K8","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-be26c83dc1cd48d4b29148df0f22ee98/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <!-- Replaces <Property name=\"TestTimeout\" value=\"30000\" /> from .testsettings -->\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <!-- Replaces the CodeCoverage DataCollector from .testsettings -->\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://Microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.dll\">\n        <Configuration>\n          <CodeCoverage />\n        </Configuration>\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-be26c83dc1cd48d4b29148df0f22ee98/local.runsettings."}],"interactionId":"2b4bc43d-aad7-4320-90bc-13ea8e5d59cf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a `.testsettings` file with three configurations:\n1. **Deployment/AssemblyResolution** - `useLoadContext=\"true\"`\n2. **TestTimeout** - 30000ms (30 seconds)\n3. **Code Coverage DataCollector**\n\nIn MSTest v3, `.testsettings` files are no longer supported. The user needs to migrate these settings to a `.runsettings` file and/or MSTest attributes.\n\nLet me provide the migration guidance:\n\n1. **TestTimeout**: Use `[Timeout(30000)]` attribute on test methods, or configure it in `.runsettings` under `<MSTest><TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout></MSTest>`.\n\n\n2. **Code Coverage**: I'll configure this in `.runsettings` under the data collection settings.\n3. **Deployment/AssemblyResolution**: These settings work differently in MSTest v3 — deployment is typically unnecessary since tests run directly from the output directory. Now I'll create a `.runsettings` file that handles the code coverage and timeout configuration.","outputTokens":801,"requestId":"0431:35CC36:1650913:17BE311:6A03376C"},"id":"c18ec2f8-e233-45d5-bf13-a4817ddb33f7","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:21:45.767Z","parentId":"f8c6d369-c0e4-46ae-be5c-5fa6554199e7"}
